      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>文王既勤止，我應受之。敷時繹思，我徂維求定。
時周之命，於繹思。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>King Wăn laboured earnestly:—
Right
is it we should have received (the kingdom).
We will diffuse (his virtue), ever cherishing the thought of ​him;
Henceforth we will seek only the settlement (of the kingdom).
It was he through whom came the appointment of Kâu.
Oh! let us ever cherish the thought of him.</seg>
      </tuv>
